@ApiAggregator_HostAddress = http://localhost:5183

### 1. Get a JWT token (any non-empty credentials are accepted in this demo)
# @name login
POST {{ApiAggregator_HostAddress}}/api/auth/token
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "alice",
  "password": "pw"
}

### Capture the token from the login response above
@token = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 2. Aggregated data from all sources (parallel fetch)
GET {{ApiAggregator_HostAddress}}/api/aggregation?city=Berlin&keyword=dotnet
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 3. Aggregation with filtering + sorting (GitHub only, by relevance desc)
GET {{ApiAggregator_HostAddress}}/api/aggregation?keyword=ai&sources=GitHub&sortBy=Relevance&sortDir=Descending
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 4. Aggregation filtered by category and date range
GET {{ApiAggregator_HostAddress}}/api/aggregation?keyword=ai&category=news&fromDate=2024-01-01&sortBy=Date&sortDir=Descending
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 5. All request statistics
GET {{ApiAggregator_HostAddress}}/api/statistics
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json

### 6. Statistics for a single API
GET {{ApiAggregator_HostAddress}}/api/statistics/GitHub
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Accept: application/json
